\subsection{All conditions and the controlled view}
\label{appendix:eval-conditions}

\Cref{sec:evaluation} reported four memory regimes (B0, NKR
depth-1, B2, deepNKR depth-3) under the benchmark-wide view. Two
additional conditions are useful for completeness:
\textbf{NKR-r3} extends NKR by chaining two depth-1 NKs (an r2
curator reads round-2 NKR failure plus the r1 NK and writes a
refinement with a \texttt{relationship\_to\_round1} field);
\textbf{B3} is a legacy mixed condition in which the downstream
agent sees a regex-extracted failure record plus a cross-task
knowledge bank (we report it for continuity with an earlier
version of this paper, but note that the regex labels make B3
strictly weaker than NKR's curator-produced records).

