\section{Case Anatomies}
\label{appendix:cases}

\paragraph{Task~003 (C-NK PASS at Agent~1).} The recipient is a
materials-property regression. Retrieval returns three records:
NK\_009 (high-MAE regression under specialty-lib substitution; the
record's \texttt{alternative} field recommends
\texttt{matminer.ElementProperty(data\_source='magpie')} with a
GradientBoostingRegressor and predict-clipping), NK\_002 (numeric
column filtering for sklearn), and PK\_007 (MLP substitute for
torch-based CGCNN). All three records were sourced from other
tasks; the leakage filter is active. Agent~1's \texttt{reasoning.md}
explicitly cites NK\_009, switches to the recommended pipeline,
clips predictions to the training range, and PASSes the official
eval at first attempt. The other two agents are not dispatched.

\paragraph{Task~058 (C-NK borderline PASS at Agent~2).} The
recipient is a syllogistic-reasoning best-fit task. Agent~1
attempts a hand-coded per-participant pipeline and fails. Agent~2,
given Agent~1's record plus the retrieved cross-task records,
performs a more exhaustive search of the input directory ($91$
tool calls vs.\ a typical $3$) and discovers
\texttt{ind\_data\_for\_plot.csv}---a pre-computed reference file
shipped in the input dataset. Agent~2 copies it to the required
output path with light reformatting. The official evaluator
accepts the output, so the team is scored as PASS, but no
modeling work was performed. We retain this case in the paper
because it illustrates a failure mode of evaluator-driven scoring
that a future ``triviality'' annotation on K records (planned
work; see \cref{sec:limitations}) should flag.

\paragraph{Task~018 (C-NK regression: PASS under C-NoShare,
fail under C-NK).} The recipient is a DILI binary-classification
task. C-NoShare's three independent agents each independently
arrive at a working Morgan-FP $+$ RandomForest pipeline and PASS.
C-NK retrieval returns NK\_002, NK\_005, and NK\_009 with scores
that exceed the topical match to the actual round-1 failure mode;
agents~1--3 spend effort on column-filtering and threshold
ablations that are irrelevant to the genuine source of failure
and run out of attempts. This is the canonical case for adding a
category-aware filter to retrieval before any production
deployment.

\section{Burgers-swept-KdV Case Study: Stress Tests and Sub-Tasks}
\label{appendix:bkdv-setup}

\paragraph{Stage~1 stress tests (14 forced-method runs).}
\textbf{Burgers shock} ($u_t + u u_x = 0$, $u_0 = -\sin(\pi x)$,
periodic on $[-1,1]$, $N_x{=}200$): A1 forced forward-Euler +
central FD at $T{=}0.5$; A2 any stable scheme at $T{=}0.1$
(pre-shock); A3 any stable scheme at $T{=}10$ (long-time
contamination). \textbf{KdV soliton}
($v_t + 6 v v_x + v_{xxx} = 0$, $v_0 = 2\,\mathrm{sech}^2(x+5)$,
periodic on $[-15,15]$, $N_x{=}256$, $T{=}2$): A4 forced explicit
RK4 + central FD for $v_{xxx}$; A5 forced Fourier spectral with
\emph{no} dealiasing; A6 forced IC amplitude $0.1$ (small-amplitude
regime). \textbf{Shallow water dam-break} ($h_t + (hu)_x = 0$,
$(hu)_t + (hu^2 + g h^2/2)_x = 0$, $g{=}1$, $h_L{=}2$, $h_R{=}1$,
$T{=}0.4$): A7 forced forward-Euler + central FD; A8 forced
Lax-Friedrichs; A9 dry-bed initial condition ($h_R{=}0$); A10
forced HLL. \textbf{Gardner}
($v_t + 6 v v_x + \tfrac{3}{2} v^2 v_x + v_{xxx} = 0$, $T{=}2$):
G1 forced explicit RK4 (IC amp $1.5$); G2 IMEX-CN spectral with
2/3 dealiasing (IC amp $1.5$); G3 IMEX-CN spectral with no
dealiasing (IC amp $1.5$); G4 IMEX-CN spectral with IC amp $3.0$
(amplitude-CFL test).

\paragraph{Stage~2 sub-task specifications.}
\textbf{T-A soliton stability:}
$u_0 = v_0^2/2 + 0.2\, v_0$, $v_0 = 2\,\mathrm{sech}^2(x+5)$,
$T{=}8$. Useful iff no NaN, $|\!\operatorname{mass}(v_T) -
\operatorname{mass}(v_0)| < 5\%$, and the final state has a
single peak with amplitude $\geq 0.7 \times$ initial.
\textbf{T-B Gaussian decomposition:}
$v_0 = 4\exp(-(x+5)^2/2.25)$, $u_0 = 0$, $T{=}6$. Useful iff no
NaN, mass drift $<5\%$, and the final state has $\geq 2$
separated local maxima with peak amplitude $\geq 1.5$.
\textbf{T-C bore-soliton interaction:}
$u_0 = 1.5\cdot(1 - \tanh(x/0.5))/2$ on $[-15,15]$,
$v_0 = 1.5\,\mathrm{sech}^2(x+8)$, $T{=}8$. Useful iff both
fields remain bounded ($\max|u|, \max|v| < 5$), the soliton peak
remains identifiable in $v$ at amplitude $\geq 0.5$, and its
position differs from a free-propagation reference by enough to
register a refractive interaction. Per-cell budget is up to three
rounds with a \texttt{finding\_record} carried across rounds
within a cell.

\section{Burgers-swept-KdV Bank Composition}
\label{appendix:bkdv-bank}

The Stage~1 bank contains 30 entries (10 positive, 20 negative)
across Burgers (5), KdV (7), shallow water (5), Gardner (9), and
four cross-domain general entries. Negative entries split on
\texttt{recommended\_action} as 13 \texttt{narrow\_claim} and 7
\texttt{change\_method}; on \texttt{scope} as 12
\texttt{regime\_bound}, 6 \texttt{general\_failure}, and 2
\texttt{local\_failure}; on \texttt{risk} as 10
\texttt{high\_risk\_false\_progress}, 8
\texttt{medium\_risk\_drift}, and 2 \texttt{low\_risk\_omission}.
The four cross-domain general entries are
(i)~``central differences fail on hyperbolic conservation laws''
(Burgers + shallow-water evidence),
(ii)~``finiteness is not accuracy'' (several runs return finite
output with wrong amplitude or spurious peaks),
(iii)~``mass conservation alone is an insufficient diagnostic
for soliton-bearing systems'' (Gardner G1/G3 both conserve mass
but the soliton is fragmented), and
(iv)~``first-order Godunov is a pre-shock baseline''. The full
bank with evidence references is shipped as a JSONL artifact
alongside the paper.

